data.description: You do not want to miss this Waterfront home that has room for your boat, RV and no HOA. Welcome home to 14605 County Road 450. This is a true gem of a home located on Lake Holly which is part of the Holly Chain of Lakes in Umatilla. The home approximately has 240 feet on the water. First time available on the market. The home sits on 5.7 acres with approximately 3 acres that are high, dry and mostly cleared with the exception of the beautiful oak trees in the front and side yard. There is a pole barn along with 3 additional sheds. Bring your RV, the home has everything you need to run your RV. New Roof 2019. The home features 2,219 square feet with 3 bedrooms 2 and 1/2 bathrooms. You have a water view from every room in the house. The home has a large kitchen with a eat-in sizeable breakfast nook, lots of cabinet space and countertops along with a pantry for easy storage. There is a traditional formal dining room for family gatherings, or you can easily use as a separate living room/ family room if you wish. The Living room is spacious for family time together and has large sliding doors that lead you to the screened in lanai so you can enjoy the amazing view of the water. The half bath is located downstairs. The living quarters is located upstairs. The Master bedroom has an en-suite bathroom with large walk-in closet. It also has an additional attached room that can easily be a nursery, office space or a quiet place to read. The laundry room is located upstairs as well. The home needs some TLC but do not let that keep you from taking a Private Tour and seeing all of the potential it has. Holly Lake is a 99 acre lake known for fishing and boating and is a part of the Holly Chain of Lakes. Call Your Realtor today! All information recorded in the MLS is intended to be accurate however, it should be independently verified by buyer and their agent.
